        <abstract>
            <p>Asks JDH’s opinion, and botanical evidence, on important law: parts that are highly developed in comparison to other allied species are very variable.</p> 
<p>Interest in hairiness of alpine plants revived by reading A. Moquin-Tandon [<hi rend="italic">Éléments de tératologie végétale</hi> (1841)]; correlation with dryness. CD seeks interpretation independent of direct environmental effect.</p> 
        </abstract>
